# WordPress PHP Standards

- Follow WordPress PHP coding standards: spaces for indentation and snake_case for function names.
- Add `defined( 'ABSPATH' ) || exit;` to direct-accessible PHP files.
- Use core APIs when available (`wp_parse_args`, `wp_json_encode`, `wp_remote_get`, etc.).
- Avoid short tags and avoid custom wrappers when core functions exist.
- Keep template files free from business logic; move logic to helpers or service-like functions.
- Prefer early returns to reduce nesting and improve readability.
- Do not use deprecated WordPress functions; replace with supported alternatives.
- For complex branches, add short comments explaining intent, not mechanics.
